			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1722">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I just finished reading Amy Wilson&rsquo;s &ldquo;<a href="/article/341">What They Taught Me</a>&rdquo; [June 2005], and I am weeping, though I don&rsquo;t know exactly why. Is it because babies are starving? Because I can&rsquo;t imagine a world where I would eat before my child has eaten? Because children are buried without a name? Am I weeping because Amy Wilson was ashamed to eat her treats from home but ate them anyway? As I read, I was eating a bowl of tofu, broccoli, and brown rice, mindlessly shoveling down the food because I felt faint from hunger, not having eaten for four hours.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Renee Ramsey<br>Half Moon Bay, California</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

			</div>
    
		<div class="article-correspondence-cta">
